## Ortus Automation

This project was scaffolded with [Ortus](https://github.com/who/ortus), which provides AI-powered development workflows including PRD-to-issues decomposition and automated implementation loops. See the ortus/ directory for scripts and prompts.

{%- if agent_cli == 'codex' %}

The primary orchestrator is `./ortus/goal.sh` — a single long-lived `codex exec "/goal CONDITION"` session that drives the queue and lets the `/goal` evaluator decide termination. `./ortus/ralph.sh` is now a one-line deprecation shim that prints a notice and `exec`s `goal.sh` with the same arguments; it is kept for one minor version so existing aliases and scripts keep working, and shares `.beads/ralph.flock` with `goal.sh` so only one orchestrator runs at a time. `./ortus/tail.sh` follows both `ralph-*.log` and `goal-*.log`. See `ortus/README.md` for the per-script reference.

The backend is resolved as `--backend` flag > `ORTUS_BACKEND` env > the `agent_cli` answer baked in at generation time (`{{ agent_cli }}` for this project), so a run can flip backends without regenerating the project.
{%- else %}

The primary orchestrator is `./ortus/goal.sh` — a single long-lived `claude -p "/goal CONDITION"` session that drives the queue and lets the `/goal` evaluator decide termination. `./ortus/ralph.sh` is now a one-line deprecation shim that prints a notice and `exec`s `goal.sh` with the same arguments; it is kept for one minor version so existing aliases and scripts keep working, and shares `.beads/ralph.flock` with `goal.sh` so only one orchestrator runs at a time. `./ortus/tail.sh` follows both `ralph-*.log` and `goal-*.log`. See `ortus/README.md` for the per-script reference.
{%- endif %}

### Scoped runs (`goal.sh -c`)

Pass `-c|--condition STR` to `goal.sh` to drive the queue until a specific milestone is reached instead of the default queue-drain condition. The evaluator judges your condition against the running transcript each turn and exits when it answers yes — useful for finishing one epic, producing a single artifact, or smoke-testing a small change end-to-end:

```bash
# Finish one epic and stop:
./ortus/goal.sh -c 'all children of bd-auth-epic are closed'

# Run until a specific report has been produced:
./ortus/goal.sh -c 'reports/release-2026-05-16.md exists and contains a go/no-go decision'

# Combine with --tasks as a hard upper bound on work attempted:
./ortus/goal.sh --tasks 5 -c 'the auth middleware migration ships cleanly'
```

Phrase the condition so a third party reading the transcript can decide pass/fail unambiguously. Keep it under the FR-004 4000-character ceiling.

